# Allow-list approach: exclude everything, then re-include only what Dockerfile needs.
# This avoids Docker enumerating 1.3 GB of project files for context comparison.
# The Dockerfile only copies: package*.json, dist/, shared/
#
# WHY: Previous "exclude list" approach made Docker walk every file in the project
# tree to check against rules, which was timing out builds at ~90s on macOS.
# The allow-list pattern lets Docker skip entire directory trees outright.

# Step 1: Exclude everything
*

# Step 2: Re-include only what the Dockerfile needs to COPY
!package.json
!package-lock.json
!dist
!shared

# Step 3: Inside re-included dirs, still strip junk
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db
**/*.swp
**/*.swo
**/*~
**/node_modules
**/.git
